{%- comment -%}
  snippets/compare-bar.liquid

  Static shell only. All content (thumbnails, counter, remove
  buttons) and all visibility/state toggling is handled at runtime
  by assets/product-card.js → initCompare() / renderCompareBar().

  IMPORTANT: render this once, globally — e.g. from layout/theme.liquid
  right before </body>:

      {% render 'compare-bar' %}

  renderCompareBar() does `document.querySelector('.compare-bar')`
  and bails out silently if it isn't found, so unlike the Quick View
  modal (which product-card.js builds and injects itself), this
  element must already exist in the page markup.

  Do not add Liquid logic, loops, or extra markup here — the JS
  owns everything inside .compare-bar__list and the counter.
  Styling already lives in theme.css (no new CSS needed).
{%- endcomment -%}
<div class="compare-bar" role="region" aria-label="Compare products">
  <div class="compare-bar__counter-wrap" aria-live="polite">
    <span class="compare-bar__counter">0</span> selected
  </div>

  <ul class="compare-bar__list" aria-label="Products selected for comparison"></ul>

  <div class="compare-bar__actions">
    <button type="button" data-compare-clear aria-label="Clear all compared products">
      Clear
    </button>
    <button type="button" data-compare-submit disabled aria-label="Compare selected products">
      Compare
    </button>
  </div>
</div>
